{
  "texts": [
    "As we progress from the direct method to the transfer strategy, and eventually to the Interlingua approach, the amount of analysis required expands.",
    "Moreover, it offers understanding of the decreasing amount of transferable knowledge required as we go up the triangle.",
    "At the literal level, a substantial quantity of data is sent, with every word imparting knowledge.",
    "Shifting guidelines are only required for parse trees and thematic objectives at the transfer level.",
    "Ultimately, at the interlingua level, a language-neutral conceptual framework that represents both the source and destination texts is encoded.The first technique, which has largely been discarded by machine translation researchers, entails incorporating all the specific information for a given language pair into a single translation direction."
  ]
}